<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
This sentence pattern is used to link sentences that are stated from the same viewpoint.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KT{{watto}}@KJ{{before^life}}ha@KJ{{heat^heart}}da<strong>shi</strong>,majimeda<strong>shi</strong>,@KJ{{sutra^verification}}mo arimasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Professor Watt is earnest and diligent and has experience.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
It is also used to state causes or reasons when there is more than one. Even if only one is stated
explictly it is implied that other causes or reasons exist.
</p>

